    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect LI bit length calculation in CSI reporting\n\n### Summary\nThe `compute_li_bitlen()` function in the NR MAC layer incorrectly calculated the Layer Indicator (LI) bit length for CSI reports. The function was using the loop index instead of the actual RI (Rank Indicator) value when determining the number of bits needed for LI encoding. This caused incorrect CSI report sizes and potential buffer overflows when processing CSI reports with multiple layers.\n\nAdditionally, the `compute_pmi_bitlen()` function had an early return statement that would terminate processing of subsequent RI values when encountering a disabled rank, instead of continuing to process all valid RI values.\n\nThese issues were causing incorrect CSI report formatting and potential crashes during CSI reporting procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Fixed `compute_li_bitlen()` to properly calculate LI bit length based on actual RI value rather than loop index\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Fixed `compute_pmi_bitlen()` to use continue instead of return when skipping disabled RI values\n\n"
}